    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Institutions devoted to the instruction of adults. Types of lyceums include specific literary institutions established in the early 19th century and those established later to provide popular lectures on literary and scientific subjects, public discussions, concerts, and other activities for furthering general education. In some nations, the term is used for universities or colleges. The term is derived from the proper name of a garden with covered walks in Athens where Aristotle taught philosophy.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instellingen die zijn gewijd aan het onderrichten van volwassenen. Er zijn verschillende soorten volksuniversiteiten, zoals de specifiek literaire instellingen die aan het begin van de 19e eeuw werden opgericht en instellingen die later werden opgericht voor algemene lezingen over literaire en wetenschappelijke onderwerpen, openbare discussies, concerten en andere activiteiten ter bevordering van algemeen onderwijs. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>開課供社會人士進修的機構，可指成立於西元十九世紀初、以文藝活動為主的機構，或指成立年代較晚、以提供社會人士延伸通識教育為目標的機構，此種機構主辦以文藝或科學為主題的演講、公共論壇、音樂會和其他活動。部分國家以此詞彙指稱大學或學院。此詞彙源自雅典一座花園之名，亞里斯多德於園中步道邊走邊講授哲學。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
